HEADWORD: Mien
<hw>Mien</hw> <pr>(m⟦emac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>mine</ets>; perh. from sane source as <ets>mener</ets> to lead; cf.
E. <ets>demean</ets>, <ets>menace</ets>, <ets>mine</ets>, n.]</ety>
<def>Aspect; air; manner; demeanor; carriage; bearing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Vice is a monster of so frightful <qex>mien</qex>,⟦br⟧
As, to be hated, needs but to be seen.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

